ding of reproductive medicine as a global phenomenon constantly in the making, situating India in the midst of, rather than peripheral to, this process.Thanks to generous funding from Fonds National Suisse de la Recherche Scientifique/Swiss National Science Foundation, the ebook editions of this book are available as Open Access volumes from Cornell Open (cornellopen.org) and other repositories.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 4aAnthropology. 4aAsian Studies. 4aConsumer Health & Fitness. 7aMEDICAL / Reproductive Medicine & Technology.2bisacsh  aReproductive technologies India, IVF in India, History of reproductive medicine, Making of IVF, Substances Anthropology, In Vitro Fertilization.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073908440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501758201zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501758201zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501758201/original  a978-3-11-073908-4 Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA